Set up Astro DB for posts:
  - [x] Install Astro DB:
    - Run: npx astro add db
  
  - [x] Create database schema:
    - Create file: db/config.ts
    - Define Posts table with columns:
      - id (number, primary key)
      - title (text)
      - pubDate (date)
      - description (text)
      - author (text)
      - imageUrl (text, optional)
      - imageAlt (text, optional)
      - tags (json, optional)
  
  - [ ] Update content config:
    - Modify or remove: src/content/config.ts
  
  - [ ] Create seed data:
    - Create file: db/seed.ts
    - Add initial post data
  
  - [ ] Update queries in pages/components:
    - Use Astro DB instead of content collections
    - Example: 
      - Import: import { db, Posts } from 'astro:db'
      - Query: const posts = await db.select().from(Posts).orderBy(Posts.pubDate)
  
  - [ ] Run development server:
    - Use command: npx astro dev
  
  - [ ] Prepare for deployment:
    - Set up Astro Studio for database hosting
  
  - [ ] General tasks:
    - [ ] Update existing pages and components to use Astro DB queries
    - [ ] Adjust data insertion logic throughout the project
  
  Resources:
  - Astro DB Documentation: https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/astro-db/